EnumInfo.Comment: When changing from 1 to 0: the maximum drive off delay time (IDN 00273) is started, drive is decelerated as best as possible according to the emergency stop deceleration (IDN 00429), followed by disabling of the torque at n min, after the drive off delay time (IDN 00207). The power stage can remain in an activated state (only possible when bit 14=1). After the maximum drive off delay time (IDN 00273) is elapsed, the locking of brake is initiated and the torque is disabled.
When changing from 0 to 1: drive follows the command values of the control unit after the drive on delay time (IDN 00206).

Object.Name: Control unit cycle time (TNcyc)
Object.Comment: The control unit cycle time defines the cyclic intervals during which the control unit makes new command values available.

Object.Name: Communication cycle time (tSync)
Object.Comment: The communication cycle time of the interface defines the intervals during which the cyclic data are transferred. It is defined as 62 us, 125 us, 250 us, ..., up to 20ms in steps of 250 s.

Object.Name: Class 1 diagnostic (C1D)
Object.Comment:
Drive shut-down error

A drive error situation of class C1D leads to the following:

  • A best case deceleration followed by torque release at nmin.
  • The drive shut-down error bit for C1D is set to '1' in the drive status (bit 13). The error bit is reset to '0' by the drive only when no errors of C1D exists and after the command 'reset class 1 diagnostic' (IDN 00099) has been received by the drive via the service channel.

Object.Name: Class 2 diagnostic (C2D)
Object.Comment: Shut-down warning (warning) When a warning is activated or canceled in the C2D, this sets the change bit for C2D in the drive status (bit 12) to a binary 1. When the C2D is read via the service channel, the C2D change bit is canceled and reset to 0.

Object.Name: Telegram type
Object.Comment: The telegram type allows selection between standard telegrams and application telegrams.

Object.Name: Configuration list of AT
Object.Comment: This IDN list contains the IDNs whose operation data will be transmitted cyclically in the AT in an application telegram. Only operation data which are present in the "IDN list of configurable data in the AT" (IDN 00187) are allowed as cyclic data.

Object.Name: IDN-list of all operation data
Object.Comment: All IDNs of all operation data, procedure commands, parameters etc. of a given drive are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: IDN-list of operation data for CP2
Object.Comment: IDNs of all operation data needed for CP2 are stored in this IDN-list and must be transferred during CP2. Processing this list is required before switching to CP3.

Object.Name: IDN-list of operation data for CP3
Object.Comment: IDNs of all operation data needed for CP3 are stored in this IDN-list and must be transferred during CP3. Processing this list is required before switching to CP4.

Object.Name: IDN-list of operation data for CP4
Object.Comment: IDNs of all operational data which can be changed during CP4 are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: IDN-list of invalid operation data for CP2
Object.Comment: IDNs which are in the list "IDN-list of operation data for CP2" (IDN 00018) and which are considered invalid by the drive prior to switchover from CP2 (SafeOp) to CP3 (PreOp) are stored in this IDN-list (see IDN 00127).

Object.Name: IDN-list of invalid operation data for CP3
Object.Comment: IDNs which are in the list "IDN-list of operation data for CP3" (IDN 00019) and which are considered invalid by the drive prior to switchover from CP3 (PreOp) to CP4 (Op) are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: Configuration list of MDT
Object.Comment: This IDN list contains the IDNs whose operation data will be transmitted cyclically in the MDT in an application telegram. Only operation data which are present in the "IDN-list of configurable data in the MDT" (IDN 00188) are allowed as cyclic data.

Object.Name: IDN-list of all procedure commands
Object.Comment: All IDNs of all drive procedure commands are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: MDT error counter
Object.Comment: The MDT error counter counts all invalid MDTs (Master Data Telegramms) in communication phase 4.

Object.Name: Manufacturer Version
Object.Comment: The operation data of the manufacturer version contains the actual firmware version and additional information of the device.

Object.Name: Hardware version
Object.Comment: The operation data of the hardware version contains the actual hardware version and additional information of the device.

Object.Name: Diagnostic message
Object.Comment: The currently relevant operating status is being monitored with diagnostic messages. The diagnostic messages are generated by the drive as a text and stored in the operation data of this IDN.

Object.Name: Sercos interface version
Object.Comment: The operation data contains the version of the SERCOS interface specification. A version number is linked to every update. If only one of the changed or new functions of the drive is supported, then the corresponding version number must be shown. Only changes or modifications of the basic functions of SERCOS interface influence the version number.

Object.Name: Length of the configurable data record in the AT
Object.Comment: The drive indicates the maximum length in bytes which can be processed in the configurable data record of the AT (Drive Telegramm)in the operation data of this IDN.

Object.Name: Length of the configurable data record in the MDT
Object.Comment: The drive indicates the maximum length in bytes which can be processed in the configurable data record of the MDT in the operation data of this IDN. The drive needs to support this IDN only if it allows the application telegram in its telegram type parameter (see IDN 00015).

Object.Name: IDN-list of configurable data in the AT
Object.Comment: This list consists of the IDNs of operation data which can be processed by the drive cyclically as feedback values.

Object.Name: IDN-list of configurable data in the MDT
Object.Comment: This list consists of the IDNs of operation data which can be processed by the drive cyclically as command values.

Object.Name: Amplifier warning temperature
Object.Comment: When the amplifier temperature exceeds the amplifier warning temperature value, the drive sets the warning bit for amplifier overtemperature in C2D (IDN 00012).

Object.Name: Amplifier shut down temperature
Object.Comment: When the amplifier temperature exceeds the amplifier shut-down temperature value, the drive sets the bit for amplifier overtemperature shut-down in C1D (IDN 00011).

Object.Name: Password
Object.Comment: SERCOS interface supports passwords that can be used to write protect selected parameters stored in the drive. IDN 00267 is used to modify passwords, as well as enable and disable write protection

Object.Name: Diagnostic numbers list
Object.Comment: The drive records every change of the diagnostic number into this list. The list is organized as a ring buffer. When the list is read via the service channel, the drive will position the last diagnostic recorded as the first element of the list.

Object.Name: DC bus voltage
Object.Comment: The drives DC (intermediate) bus voltage value is placed in this parameter.

Object.Name: DC bus current
Object.Comment: The drive places the measured (actual) DC (intermediate) bus current in this parameter.

Object.Name: Amplifier temperature
Object.Comment: The drive places the measured (actual) amplifier temperature (output stage) in this parameter.

Object.Name: Diagnostic number
Object.Comment: For every diagnostic, the drive stores a manufacturer specific code in the diagnostic number parameter. Using this, the operator interface has the ability to display diagnostic message text in languages not supported by the drive

Object.Name: Syncronisation mode
Object.Comment: With this IDN is it possible to set the IO-Synchronisation mode. The default is "Use DC's, Watchdog ON, Level 0". In this mode synchronisation problems generate an error. With choosing "Level 1" the error limit is increased. This level should only be used for systems where the IO synchronsation is not stable. This level could not be used if the position interface is configured.
